  'calc.vw.wiz.1':'Instructions','calc.vw.wiz.2':'Load data','calc.vw.wiz.3':'Results',
  'calc.vw.what.title':'What is the Van Westendorp PSM?',
  'calc.vw.what.desc':'The Price Sensitivity Meter (PSM) is a technique developed by Peter van Westendorp (1976) to identify the psychologically acceptable price range for a product or service. Based on 4 open-ended questions, it generates price-perception curves that reveal the lower and upper limits of the acceptable range, the optimal price, and the indifference price.',
  'calc.vw.what.note':'The model <strong>does not require</strong> showing prices to the respondent beforehand. Respondents freely imagine what price corresponds to each perception.',
  'calc.vw.field.title':'How to apply the questions in the field',
  'calc.vw.field.desc':'The 4 questions must be asked in this order, after presenting the product concept. Record the answer as a number (without currency symbol).',
  'calc.vw.q1':'At what price does this product seem <em>so cheap</em> that you would doubt its quality? <br><small style="color:var(--ink3)">(Column: <strong>muy_barato</strong>)</small>',
  'calc.vw.q2':'At what price does this product seem <em>cheap</em> and a good buy?<br><small style="color:var(--ink3)">(Column: <strong>barato</strong>)</small>',
  'calc.vw.q3':'At what price does this product start to seem <em>expensive</em>, though you would still consider it?<br><small style="color:var(--ink3)">(Column: <strong>caro</strong>)</small>',
  'calc.vw.q4':'At what price does this product seem <em>so expensive</em> that you would definitely not buy it?<br><small style="color:var(--ink3)">(Column: <strong>muy_caro</strong>)</small>',
  'calc.vw.consistency':'<strong>Consistency rule:</strong> muy_barato ≤ barato ≤ caro ≤ muy_caro. Responses that do not meet this condition will be automatically excluded from the analysis.',
  'calc.vw.format.title':'Excel file format',
  'calc.vw.format.desc':'The file must have exactly these columns (names must match):',
