  'calc.nms.title':'VW + Newton-Miller-Smith Extension (NMS)',
  'calc.nms.desc':'The NMS extension (1993) adds 2 purchase-intent questions to the classic PSM. This allows building approximate demand and revenue curves, identifying the price with maximum sales volume and the price that maximizes revenue.',
  'calc.nms.note':'The NMS extension <strong>calibrates</strong> PSM responses toward more realistic behavior, correcting respondents\' tendency to overstate acceptable prices.',
  'calc.nms.q.title':'The 6 questions of the NMS instrument',
  'calc.nms.q.desc':'The first 4 are identical to the classic PSM. The 2 additional ones use the prices the respondent themselves indicated as reference.',
  'calc.nms.q5':'If this product cost <em>[the "cheap" price the respondent indicated]</em>, how likely are you to buy it in the next 6 months?<br><small style="color:var(--ink3)">Scale 1–5: 1=Definitely not · 2=Probably not · 3=Undecided · 4=Probably yes · 5=Definitely yes<br>(Column: <strong>intent_barato</strong>)</small>',
  'calc.nms.q6':'If this product cost <em>[the "expensive" price the respondent indicated]</em>, how likely are you to buy it in the next 6 months?<br><small style="color:var(--ink3)">Scale 1–5: 1=Definitely not · 2=Probably not · 3=Undecided · 4=Probably yes · 5=Definitely yes<br>(Column: <strong>intent_caro</strong>)</small>',
  'calc.nms.important':'<strong>Important in the field:</strong> Questions 5 and 6 must be presented with each respondent\'s personalized price (the one they indicated in Q2 and Q3 respectively). In paper surveys, the interviewer writes down the price before asking the question.',
  'calc.nms.format.desc':'6 data columns (besides ID). Intent columns range from 1 to 5.',
